cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY

The paper focuses on the security aspect of backscatter communication for on-body wearable and implantable devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the study of propagation paths and signatures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the implementation of the design in a software radio and evaluation of different backscatter tags indicate that it could also belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
